        "theme":  "Philosophy",
        "summary":  "Research by Boston University professor Emma Wiles finds that framing AI agents as employees or colleagues causes humans to catch 18% fewer errors and reduces personal accountability. Major tech companies are increasingly marketing AI agents as digital coworkers, but experts warn this anthropomorphization undermines the human oversight essential in healthcare, government, and enterprise operations. The article calls for industry norms that preserve human responsibility in AI-assisted workflows.",
