        "execSummary":  "Google DeepMind\u0027s $10 million bet on multi-agent safety research signals that even the most advanced AI labs view agent orchestration at scale as an unsolved and potentially dangerous problem. For enterprise leaders building agentic workflows ΓÇö especially those involving customer-facing agents, financial transactions, or sensitive data ΓÇö the risk categories identified (scams, prompt injection, emergent coordination failures) are not hypothetical. This is a strategic flag to ensure agent orchestration architectures include human-in-the-loop checkpoints and adversarial testing before scaling. Note that Google has both a safety motivation and a competitive interest in being seen as the responsible leader in agentic AI infrastructure.",
